<item>
            <title>[JOHNZON-59] broken mapping of generic types in inheritence hierarchy</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JOHNZON-59</link>
                <project id="12315523" key="JOHNZON">Johnzon</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We heavily use json for saving arbitrary objects as json-string in database.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;if you have a inheritance hierarchy of more than 1 with a generic declaration, deserializing the string fails with&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;ClassCastException - &lt;tt&gt;Cannot cast sun.reflect.generics.reflectiveObjects.TypeVariableImpl to java.lang.Class&lt;/tt&gt; if the JavaType f.e. java.util.Long was serialized as a JsonString&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;MapperException: &lt;tt&gt;Unable to parse 478965 to T&lt;/tt&gt; if the JavaType was serialized as JsonNumber&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;maybe this is a follow up error from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JOHNZON-56&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;JOHNZON-56&lt;/a&gt; but since this got release I decided to create a new issue.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
